A potato is a starchy, root vegetable that is widely grown and consumed around the world. Potatoes are a good source of dietary fiber, vitamins, and minerals, making them a nutritious and versatile food. They are generally oval or round in shape and have a thin, brownish skin that covers the white or yellowish flesh inside. Potatoes can be cooked in a variety of ways, including boiling, baking, frying, and roasting. They are often used as a side dish or a main ingredient in dishes such as mashed potatoes, potato salad, and French fries. Potatoes are also a popular ingredient in snacks such as chips and crisps. Due to their widespread availability, affordability, and nutritional benefits, potatoes are a staple food in many cultures around the world.